cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the application of NOMA to improve the spectral efficiency of a multi-user network with mixed multicasting and unicasting traffic. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of beamforming and power allocation to improve the performance of multicast-unicast streaming. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new scheme for managing the transmission of multicast and unicast messages in a network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with streaming of mixed multicast and unicast traffic. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also relevant as the paper investigates the security enhancements of using NOMA for multicast-unicast streaming.
